  "text": "The Kubernetes API deprecation policy is enforced across multiple components in the kube-apiserver codebase (v1.32.0):\n\n## Deprecation Warning Injection\nThe primary component is `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/deprecation/deprecation.go`, which defines core interfaces and functions for handling API deprecation. It exports `IsDeprecated()`, `WarningMessage()`, and `RemovedRelease()` functions that check for deprecated API versions and generate appropriate warning messages.\n\nIn `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` (lines 788-794), the API installer invokes these deprecation checks during resource handler registration. It calls `deprecation.MajorMinor()` to parse the current version, then `deprecation.IsDeprecated()` to check if a resource is deprecated, and finally `deprecation.WarningMessage()` and `deprecation.RemovedRelease()` to generate the warning text.\n\nThe warnings are then injected into HTTP responses through `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/warning/warning.go` via the `AddWarningsHandler()` function, which uses a restful handler to add warnings to the context. The actual warning headers are written via `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/warning.go`, which implements a `WithWarningRecorder` handler that deduplicates and adds Warning headers to responses with proper truncation handling.\n\n## Removal Version Validation\nThe removal version validation and removal of served API versions is handled in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/deleted_kinds.go`. This file defines the `ResourceExpirationEvaluator` interface with two critical methods: `RemoveDeletedKinds()` and `ShouldServeForVersion()`. The evaluator checks the `removedInterface` (which exposes `APILifecycleRemoved()` method) to determine if an API should no longer be served.\n\nThe enforcement chain begins in `pkg/controlplane/apiserver/apis.go` (line 113), which calls `resourceExpirationEvaluator.RemoveDeletedKinds()` to remove storage for deprecated API versions that have reached their removal deadline. When the removal version is equal to the current version in a GA release (or in alpha with `strictRemovedHandlingInAlpha` set), the API is not served.\n\n## Minimum Supported API Version Checks\nMinimum supported API version checks are enforced in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go`. The `selectStorageVersions()` function (lines 173-190) checks the `introducedInterface` (which exposes `APILifecycleIntroduced()` method) to ensure API resources are not used before their introduction version. If an introduced version is greater than the current compatibility version, that version is skipped.\n\n## Custom Resource Definition Deprecation\nFor CustomResourceDefinitions, `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_handler.go` handles deprecation at lines 1019-1026. It checks the `Deprecated` flag on CRD versions and generates deprecation warnings either from the `DeprecationWarning` field or by calling `defaultDeprecationWarning()` if no custom warning is provided.\n\n## Metrics Tracking\nDeprecated API requests are tracked via `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go`, which records metrics for deprecated API usage and removal release information through the `InstrumentRouteFunc()` calls in the installer.\n\nThese components work together to enforce the complete API deprecation lifecycle: warning users about deprecated APIs, preventing removed APIs from being served, and ensuring APIs are not used before their introduction version."
}

